	<key>A couple of metrics depend on which Apple Watch you wear. Wrist temperature, which feeds skin temp, arrived with Series 8, so older watches don't report it. Blood oxygen is the bigger one: Apple removed the SpO₂ sensor from the newest US units over a patent dispute, so those simply don't measure it.</key>
